      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOUSLED CROWN (1) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1600m at Port Hedland, beaten 5 lengths into sixth after being prominent at the bend. Looks well placed so expect a big run this time. HUNDRED YARDS (4) showed early speed from a good draw last time and led until they straightened, eventually finishing fourth and beaten 2.5 lengths over 1600m at Port Hedland. Expected to be in this for a long way. FRIES WITH THAT (5) finds it hard to win but was in the finish last time when beaten 0.9 lengths into second over 1406m at this track. Has the pace to be in a prominent position from the outset. Sure to be competitive. GRUNDY THREE VOTES (3) was beaten 5.5 lengths into eighth at the second run back from a break in a 1205m contest at this track at his latest appearance. Has his share of ability and is a top-three prospect. BAY STREET (6) can improve third-up into the campaign.",
